raw_data.description: Act as part of a Country Professional Services team, work productively with Consultants, Architects, Project Managers, and other internal interfaces to ensure that the customer succeeds in their objectives. raw_data.title: Fellow Solution Architect
raw_data.description: Act as part of a Professional Services team, work productively with Consultants, Architects, Project Managers, and other internal & external interfaces to ensure that the customer succeeds in their objectives. As an Enterprise Lead Architect resource, responsible for the translation of business requirements into specific process aligned designs for the Siemens PLM Software solution based on multi product/multi industry domain knowledge and best practices, for strategic and complex Enterprise Programs Globally, in order for the Siemens PLM Software to deliver market leading solutions and provide value to the customer. Work with Product Development in the creation of the product roadmap and influence the design of new product functionality and industry solutions. Completely in line with program & project processes and messaging, interact with the customer to support the management of customer expectations and support customer adoption by leveraging the complete Siemens Delivery framework. Provide architectural guidance and advice complex and/ or strategic global Sales/PreSales pursuits and Services projects, through the complexity of solution architecture options and the long term roadmap for the solution. Act as ultimate authority on architectural design to address business problems, and help define and drive their long term PLM roadmap as part of the strategic account plan for the customer and ensuring that the technical integrity of the solution remains aligned to requirements and value delivery throughout project and that the various project solutions will work together to deliver value. Provides direction for process design, process integration and process change activities either internally or at customer sites. Leverage relevant templates in the leadership of project solutions in own specialist area worldwide, and curate best practices and templates, providing mentoring in the creation and adoption of templates and solutions within the SPLM Delivery Framework. Works under self management and will determine solutions, methods and procedures on enterprise assignments/projects globally of highest complexity and diverse scope that require specialist architectural expertise and leadership. Provides guidance and mentoring to other architects within and beyond immediate project or program, on the architecture of multi -domain PLM solutions to other Services Solution Architects and consultants globally. Lead Global Solution Architecture Community of Practice, promoting adoption into the Zones and ensuring that knowledge and lessons learnt are shared across Zone boundaries. May undertake some people management activities for a team as applicable.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: BS/BA in related discipline or equivalent combination of experience and education

labor_categories.years_experience: BS/BA in related discipline or equivalent combination of experience and education
